BTree - package BTree
 
BTree - Class in BTree
This class is the implementation for a B+ Tree.
Each node contains the data (the keys), a pointer to its parent, pointers to each of the children, and if the node is a leaf, a pointer to its right neighbor.
The user can get the root node, which is the root of the tree.
BTree() - Constructor for class BTree.BTree
Constructs a B+ Tree of order 1
BTree(int) - Constructor for class BTree.BTree
Constructs a B+ Tree of order ord
BTreeHandler - Class in BTree
This class is used for writing the current BTree onto disk and reading data from disk to create a BTree in memory, since BTree is serializable.
